metadata.name: Settings::TwoFactorAuthentication::OtpAuthenticationController POST #create when signed in when user has OTP enabled when creation succeeds redirects to code confirmation page without updating user secret and setting otp secret in the session

sql_query.sql: SELECT "users"."id", "users"."email", "users"."created_at", "users"."updated_at", "users"."encrypted_password", "users"."reset_password_token", "users"."reset_password_sent_at", "users"."sign_in_count", "users"."current_sign_in_at", "users"."last_sign_in_at", "users"."admin", "users"."confirmation_token", "users"."confirmed_at", "users"."confirmation_sent_at", "users"."unconfirmed_email", "users"."locale", "users"."encrypted_otp_secret", "users"."encrypted_otp_secret_iv", "users"."encrypted_otp_secret_salt", "users"."consumed_timestep", "users"."otp_required_for_login", "users"."last_emailed_at", "users"."otp_backup_codes", "users"."account_id", "users"."disabled", "users"."moderator", "users"."invite_id", "users"."chosen_languages", "users"."created_by_application_id", "users"."approved", "users"."sign_in_token", "users"."sign_in_token_sent_at", "users"."webauthn_id", "users"."sign_up_ip", "users"."role_id", "users"."settings", "users"."time_zone" FROM "users" WHERE "users"."id" = $1 ORDER BY "users"."id" ASC LIMIT $2
